WEBVTT

00:12.512 --> 00:15.598
- Okay ladies,
this is the spot.

00:15.598 --> 00:16.683
- Thanks, Charlie.

00:16.683 --> 00:18.017
- This is so exciting.

00:18.017 --> 00:19.602
I can't believe I'm
actually doing this.

00:19.602 --> 00:21.771
Like a 400 year old shipwreck.

00:21.771 --> 00:24.232
- A 400 year old
Spanish shipwreck

00:24.232 --> 00:27.610
that's never been seen and
never been photographed.

00:27.610 --> 00:28.862
- Do you think there's
gold down there

00:28.862 --> 00:30.655
or is that just an old legend?

00:32.657 --> 00:34.951
- Please tell me I didn't
forget my extra battery.

00:34.951 --> 00:37.620
- Hey Alex, what do
you think dad would say

00:37.620 --> 00:40.331
if he knew I finally got
my dive certification?

00:40.331 --> 00:41.875
- I think he'd be really happy.

00:42.834 --> 00:44.294
Hey Charlie?
- Yo.

00:44.294 --> 00:45.879
- What is the visibility?

00:45.879 --> 00:46.796
- At least 80 feet.

00:46.796 --> 00:49.466
- Aha, that's what
I like to hear.

00:49.466 --> 00:50.675
These photos are
going to be perfect.

00:50.675 --> 00:53.553
- Oh, this is so exciting,
my first big dive.

00:53.553 --> 00:56.598
- I know and I'm glad
we're doing this together.

00:56.598 --> 00:58.600
- Oh yeah, it makes
me way less nervous.

00:58.600 --> 01:01.060
- Don't be nervous, you
just stick with me, okay?

01:01.060 --> 01:02.812
You're gonna do great.

01:02.812 --> 01:04.814
You're gonna love it down there.

01:04.814 --> 01:07.275
- Okay
girls, here we go.

01:07.275 --> 01:08.151
- You ready?

01:27.796 --> 01:29.672
- These are gorgeous, Alex.

01:30.423 --> 01:32.258
The composition, perfect.

01:32.258 --> 01:33.134
- Thank you.

01:33.134 --> 01:34.552
- The sense of
detail, exquisite.

01:34.552 --> 01:35.386
- Thank you.

01:35.386 --> 01:36.471
- The lighting's
like a painting.

01:36.471 --> 01:37.931
- I don't know what
else to say, Sharon.

01:37.931 --> 01:39.140
It is some of my best work.

01:39.140 --> 01:40.475
- But they're two days late.

01:40.475 --> 01:43.436
- I know, but I just wanted
the photos to be perfect.

01:43.436 --> 01:45.396
- I had to use Ben's
Swiss orchard shots.

01:45.396 --> 01:46.397
- What?
- And you know I didn't want

01:46.397 --> 01:48.650
to use Ben's Swiss
orchard shots.

01:48.650 --> 01:49.776
Do you know what
your problem is?

01:49.776 --> 01:51.778
- No, but I'm sure
you're gonna tell me.

01:51.778 --> 01:53.655
- You're too much
of a perfectionist.

01:53.655 --> 01:55.657
- I happen to think
that perfectionism

01:55.657 --> 01:57.283
is an admirable quality.

01:57.283 --> 01:59.452
- What did I say last week?

01:59.452 --> 02:02.121
- You said that this
shoot could be my ticket

02:02.121 --> 02:03.331
to the Creative
Director position.

02:03.331 --> 02:04.123
- That's right.

02:04.123 --> 02:05.458
You have a lot of great ideas

02:05.458 --> 02:07.585
about the types of
stories we should do.

02:07.585 --> 02:10.505
And I know you're dying
for more creative control.

02:10.505 --> 02:12.632
But how can I trust you
to put an issue together

02:12.632 --> 02:15.051
when you miss your
own deadlines?

02:16.135 --> 02:17.262
Do you know what this is?

02:17.262 --> 02:18.721
- A list of all the
deadlines I've missed?

02:18.721 --> 02:20.723
- Funny.

02:20.723 --> 02:22.600
It's Ben Watson's resume.

02:22.600 --> 02:24.811
He wants to be
Creative Director, too.

02:24.811 --> 02:25.728
- Ben Watson?

02:25.728 --> 02:27.772
Oh come on, Sharon,
you even told me

02:27.772 --> 02:29.649
I had a better eye than Ben.

02:29.649 --> 02:30.817
And plus, most of his photos

02:30.817 --> 02:32.652
don't even make it
to the magazine.

02:33.570 --> 02:35.321
Except for those
apple tree shots.

02:35.321 --> 02:37.574
- Do you know what he
has, that you don't?

02:37.574 --> 02:39.701
Organization and discipline.

02:39.701 --> 02:41.369
- Sharon,
the meeting's starting.

02:41.369 --> 02:42.620
- I'll be right there.

02:43.329 --> 02:45.290
Now if you'll excuse me.

02:45.290 --> 02:48.084
The cover story for our
30th anniversary issue

02:48.084 --> 02:51.170
fell through and I have to
figure something out fast.

02:51.170 --> 02:53.840
I'm thinking 30 of
the best scenic views

02:53.840 --> 02:55.675
or something like that.

02:55.675 --> 02:57.302
I don't know, it'll come to me.

03:16.195 --> 03:19.032
- There, look how
organized I am.

03:28.374 --> 03:29.417
Huh, pearls.

03:32.712 --> 03:35.298
Legend of the Blue
Polynesian Pearl.

03:38.259 --> 03:39.260
- Hey Alex.

03:40.845 --> 03:42.555
- Ben, hey.

03:44.641 --> 03:47.644
Congratulations on your
shots making the cover.

03:47.644 --> 03:48.603
- Thanks.

03:48.603 --> 03:49.896
- Yeah, it was great.

03:52.565 --> 03:53.733
Can I help you?

03:53.733 --> 03:56.569
Just like I'm busy here.

03:56.569 --> 03:58.196
- Did Sharon tell you
the idea I pitched

03:58.196 --> 03:59.656
for the anniversary issue?

03:59.656 --> 04:00.740
- Nope.

04:01.950 --> 04:03.326
- Chan Dan Ya.

04:03.326 --> 04:04.535
- What's that?

04:04.535 --> 04:06.871
- It's a cliff in China
that spits out a stone egg

04:06.871 --> 04:08.581
once every 30 years.

04:09.415 --> 04:12.001
Perfect for the 30th
anniversary, don't you think?

04:14.671 --> 04:15.713
- Ah...

04:15.713 --> 04:16.798
Hello?

04:17.799 --> 04:18.716
That's my sister.

04:22.095 --> 04:24.806
Yeah, how are you?

04:24.806 --> 04:25.682
Renee, I...

04:27.642 --> 04:29.560
Tourists began flocking to Fiji

04:29.560 --> 04:31.437
to find the pearl
after the release

04:31.437 --> 04:33.815
of the bestselling
book Pearl in Paradise.

04:33.815 --> 04:35.441
Although it has
never been found,

04:35.441 --> 04:37.485
locals believe the
rare pearl is buried

04:37.485 --> 04:41.489
somewhere in the
rainforests of Viti Levu.

04:44.909 --> 04:45.618
Huh?

04:58.298 --> 04:59.465
- When's the next book
coming out, Colin?

04:59.465 --> 05:01.009
If you don't mind me asking.

05:01.009 --> 05:02.135
- Why thank you, Molly.

05:02.135 --> 05:03.970
You know I just turned
in the final draft

05:03.970 --> 05:05.930
to the editor, so with
editor notes and all that,

05:05.930 --> 05:07.890
mid, probably February.

05:07.890 --> 05:09.100
- Did you decide on a title?

05:09.100 --> 05:10.101
- I did.

05:11.310 --> 05:15.606
Treasures in Taipei, but
shh, don't tell anybody.

05:15.606 --> 05:17.275
- Blake Montoya
goes to Asia, huh?

05:17.275 --> 05:18.443
Cool.

05:18.443 --> 05:20.987
You've probably been there
a million times anyway.

05:20.987 --> 05:22.697
Usual raspberry scone and jam?

05:22.697 --> 05:24.073
- Yeah, you know what,
I'm gonna wait though

05:24.073 --> 05:24.949
until my agent gets here.

05:24.949 --> 05:26.534
She should be here any minute.

05:27.410 --> 05:28.286
Thank you, Molly.

05:31.581 --> 05:33.875
- Colin Page, nice to meet you.

05:34.959 --> 05:36.044
- Who are you?

05:36.044 --> 05:37.587
- Rita didn't tell you?

05:37.587 --> 05:39.881
I'm Derek Foster and I'm
gonna be working closely

05:39.881 --> 05:41.299
with you from now on.

05:44.010 --> 05:46.220
- Rita's been my
agent for 10 years

05:46.220 --> 05:48.848
and now I'm getting passed
off to a junior agent?

05:48.848 --> 05:51.350
- No, she'll remained involved.

05:51.350 --> 05:53.186
It'll just allow her to
focus on a few clients

05:53.186 --> 05:54.687
that need more
attention right now.

05:54.687 --> 05:57.106
Trust me, though,
you're in good hands.

05:57.106 --> 05:58.357
- Sir,
what can I get you?

05:58.357 --> 05:59.484
- What are you drinking?

05:59.484 --> 06:02.278
- It's an organic Ceylon
tea from Sri Lanka.

06:03.780 --> 06:04.781
- He brings his own.

06:04.781 --> 06:06.991
- Just a regular
coffee, two Splendas.

06:07.825 --> 06:10.703
I'm not gonna lie to you,
I'm a really big fan.

06:10.703 --> 06:11.871
- Really?

06:11.871 --> 06:13.039
- Yeah.

06:13.039 --> 06:15.041
You've got a couple really
remarkable successes.

06:15.041 --> 06:18.377
Pearl in Paradise sold 23,000
copies in its first week.

06:18.377 --> 06:20.046
It's impressive.

06:20.046 --> 06:21.547
Impressive for eight years ago.

06:22.673 --> 06:24.884
- Okay, eight years ago
you were in high school.

06:24.884 --> 06:26.385
- I'm wise beyond my years.

06:26.385 --> 06:27.845
Let's talk facts,
you're last three books

06:27.845 --> 06:29.597
have tapered off dramatically.

06:30.389 --> 06:31.641
- I wouldn't say dramatically.

06:31.641 --> 06:33.893
- The sales report, the
last two barely sold enough

06:33.893 --> 06:35.394
to stay on the shelves.

06:35.394 --> 06:36.479
Online was even worse.

06:36.479 --> 06:39.899
Diamonds in Dubai
made 2,000 downloads.

06:40.733 --> 06:42.235
What's going on C. P.?

06:42.235 --> 06:43.069
Talk to me.

06:43.069 --> 06:45.154
- What are you my therapist now?

06:45.154 --> 06:47.573
- Look, I read your manuscript
for Treasures in Taipei.

06:47.573 --> 06:49.951
And I can see why the
publisher's rejecting it.

06:49.951 --> 06:52.120
- What, they rejected it?

06:52.120 --> 06:54.413
- Editor thought it
was a greatest hits

06:54.413 --> 06:55.206
of all your old stuff.

06:55.206 --> 06:56.249
Same ole, same ole.

06:56.249 --> 06:57.583
She wants new.

06:57.583 --> 06:59.168
She wants fresh and
I agree with her.

06:59.168 --> 07:01.129
You really, really
played it safe.

07:01.129 --> 07:03.923
- I have never had a
manuscript rejected from Rita.

07:03.923 --> 07:05.258
- Just rewrite it.

07:05.258 --> 07:07.510
Get rid of Blake Montoya
and create a new character

07:07.510 --> 07:09.887
with higher stakes.
- No, I can't get rid of him.

07:09.887 --> 07:12.598
Blake Montoya, the fans
like Blake Montoya.

07:12.598 --> 07:15.268
They love Blake, they're
not just gonna spend pages

07:15.268 --> 07:16.060
learning a new char...

07:16.060 --> 07:16.894
I'm calling Rita.

07:16.894 --> 07:18.187
- Now look, Rita brought me in

07:18.187 --> 07:19.647
to help you find a new approach.

07:19.647 --> 07:21.440
We have to reinvent
you as an author.

07:21.440 --> 07:24.318
If you trust me, I can
help you make a comeback.

07:24.318 --> 07:25.653
- And if I don't?

07:25.653 --> 07:27.738
- The publisher
is gonna drop you.

07:27.738 --> 07:28.781
And Rita will, too.

07:29.699 --> 07:30.783
- Oh boy.

07:34.620 --> 07:36.747
- Sharon, check this out.

07:37.582 --> 07:40.960
What is the traditional 30th
wedding anniversary gift?

07:40.960 --> 07:42.295
- Is this a rhetorical question

07:42.295 --> 07:44.088
or do you actually
want me to guess?

07:44.088 --> 07:45.339
- Pearls.

07:45.339 --> 07:48.301
Pearls, for the cover of
the anniversary issue.

07:48.301 --> 07:49.802
So there is this rare blue pearl

07:49.802 --> 07:53.639
buried somewhere in Fiji and
I'm gonna be the one to find it

07:53.639 --> 07:56.100
and I'm gonna photograph
the entire thing.

07:56.100 --> 07:58.394
- And how are you gonna do that?

07:58.394 --> 07:59.353
- Glad you asked.

07:59.353 --> 08:01.480
So there's this guy
named Colin Page

08:01.480 --> 08:03.858
and he wrote a
romance-adventure book

08:03.858 --> 08:04.942
about eight years ago.

08:04.942 --> 08:06.110
International best seller.

08:06.110 --> 08:06.986
- Pearl in Paradise.

08:06.986 --> 08:08.321
- Yes.
- I love that book.

08:08.321 --> 08:10.156
- Okay, so in the
forward, he claims

08:10.156 --> 08:13.326
to be the only person who
knows where this pearl is.

08:14.577 --> 08:16.329
- Fantastic idea, Alex.

08:16.996 --> 08:18.831
You take the photos,
he'll handle the writing.

08:18.831 --> 08:21.000
Call this guy's agent and find
out how soon he can leave.

08:21.000 --> 08:21.834
- No, no, no, no.

08:21.834 --> 08:22.710
- Problem?

08:22.710 --> 08:24.420
- Well, I was just
gonna call him

08:24.420 --> 08:26.797
and interview him and then
I was gonna go on my own.

08:26.797 --> 08:28.174
- He's a best selling author.

08:28.174 --> 08:30.718
Can you imagine the guest
piece he'll come up with?

08:30.718 --> 08:32.386
- But I sort of imagined

08:32.386 --> 08:34.514
this first person
photographic narrative

08:34.514 --> 08:36.641
of my journey through
the rainforest,

08:36.641 --> 08:38.768
which would parallel
my emotional journey.

08:41.520 --> 08:43.189
I'll take the photos and
he can do the writing.

08:43.189 --> 08:45.733
- Great idea, glad
you thought of it.

08:45.733 --> 08:46.525
- Huh.

08:46.525 --> 08:47.860
- Have you read the book?

08:47.860 --> 08:50.029
- Yeah, yeah.

08:50.029 --> 08:52.281
- You should read the book.

08:52.281 --> 08:53.115
- Yeah.

08:56.869 --> 09:01.832
Hey Sharon, look I know I,
I know I really messed up,

09:01.832 --> 09:04.543
but if I can prove to
you that I am disciplined

09:04.543 --> 09:06.254
and organized enough
to pull this off,

09:06.254 --> 09:09.340
will you give me the
Creative Director position?

09:09.340 --> 09:10.716
- You'd certainly have an edge.

09:11.759 --> 09:13.010
- Is that a yes?

09:13.010 --> 09:14.262
- An edge.

09:14.262 --> 09:15.137
- I'll take it.

09:21.644 --> 09:23.396
- I'm not going to Fiji.

09:24.397 --> 09:26.190
Well no, I'm busy.

09:26.190 --> 09:28.150
I don't have six days to traipse

09:28.150 --> 09:30.820
around a rainforest
looking for a pearl.

09:30.820 --> 09:31.988
- I know you're a homebody,

09:31.988 --> 09:34.782
but National Discoveries
has 2.5 million readers.

09:34.782 --> 09:36.659
That's 2.5 million
people who will remember

09:36.659 --> 09:38.077
what a talented writer you are.

09:38.077 --> 09:39.912
That's 2.5 million
additional people

09:39.912 --> 09:41.789
to buy Taipei when it comes out.

09:41.789 --> 09:43.124
- It's a bad idea.

09:43.124 --> 09:44.667
- No, it's a good idea.

09:44.667 --> 09:46.794
You know where the
pearl is, now go get it.

09:47.670 --> 09:49.171
Oh wait, oh no, you didn't lie

09:49.171 --> 09:51.132
about the pearl
being real, did you?

09:51.132 --> 09:52.425
- No, no, no.

09:52.425 --> 09:56.220
I mean I have never seen it,
but I'm sure that it exists.

09:56.220 --> 09:57.722
- And you know
where it's buried?

09:57.722 --> 10:01.851
- Well see, I might
have oversold that part,

10:01.851 --> 10:02.768
just a little bit.

10:02.768 --> 10:04.562
- Can you find it
on Google Maps?

10:04.562 --> 10:08.733
- Look, can we please just
pass on this article idea?

10:08.733 --> 10:10.067
- Listen to me, C. P.

10:10.067 --> 10:11.777
- Please don't call me that.

10:11.777 --> 10:14.697
- I told you it doesn't matter
how fantastic the rewrite is

10:14.697 --> 10:15.990
if no one buys it.

10:15.990 --> 10:17.825
This article is the thing
we need to save your career.

10:17.825 --> 10:21.162
I'll forward your boarding
pass, you leave tomorrow.

10:21.162 --> 10:22.538
- Hello?

10:25.666 --> 10:26.625
Fiji.

10:31.505 --> 10:33.716
- Are you sure you're okay
apartment sitting for me

10:33.716 --> 10:35.176
for like the millionth time?

10:35.176 --> 10:36.469
- Of course.

10:37.636 --> 10:39.472
- Hey, have you,

10:39.472 --> 10:41.682
have you seen my Merino socks?

10:41.682 --> 10:44.685
- I have no idea what
you just asked me.

10:44.685 --> 10:45.728
- Found 'em.

10:45.728 --> 10:47.313
- Okay, so legend
has it that the pearl

10:47.313 --> 10:49.106
comes from a clam
instead of an oyster,

10:49.106 --> 10:50.483
which makes it more rare.

10:50.483 --> 10:51.525
- Yeah, I know.

10:51.525 --> 10:52.902
- How are you gonna find it?

10:52.902 --> 10:56.739
- A few good maps, an expert
guide, maybe a little faith.

10:56.739 --> 10:58.366
- And what will you do with it?

10:58.366 --> 11:01.619
- I think I would just donate
it to a museum in Fiji.

11:01.619 --> 11:03.829
Yeah, I think people
need to see it.

11:03.829 --> 11:05.790
Plus, it's not about the money,

11:05.790 --> 11:08.000
I just want the promotion.

11:08.000 --> 11:09.418
- I don't understand
why you want

11:09.418 --> 11:11.504
to be Creative Director so bad.

11:11.504 --> 11:13.339
You're gonna be home a lot more,

11:13.339 --> 11:16.258
not traveling as
much, managing staff.

11:16.258 --> 11:17.218
- I know.

11:17.218 --> 11:19.136
I know, Renee, but I just,

11:19.136 --> 11:21.806
I wanna inspire people
to go on adventures.

11:21.806 --> 11:23.516
You know, go see the world.

11:23.516 --> 11:26.268
Experience it, try new things.

11:26.268 --> 11:28.938
Exactly how dad
inspired me, you know?

11:28.938 --> 11:30.481
- Yeah, yeah I do.

11:31.816 --> 11:35.027
So wait, are you saying
that your globetrotting days

11:35.027 --> 11:37.738
are behind you and you're
ready to settle down?

11:37.738 --> 11:39.365
- No.

11:39.365 --> 11:41.242
- Okay, so listen to this.

11:41.242 --> 11:43.411
If a couple finds
this pearl together,

11:43.411 --> 11:46.247
it's true love and they're
destined to be married.

11:47.957 --> 11:50.042
So who's this guy you're
meeting up with again?

11:50.042 --> 11:51.293
- Stop it.

11:51.293 --> 11:52.253
I know what you're doing.

11:53.337 --> 11:55.005
Here, this is his book.

11:57.216 --> 11:59.677
- A Blake Montoya Adventure.

12:03.347 --> 12:05.850
Okay, so if this guy
claims to be the only one

12:05.850 --> 12:07.017
who knows where the pearl is,

12:07.017 --> 12:08.227
why didn't he bring
it back with him?

12:08.227 --> 12:09.687
- I don't know.

12:09.687 --> 12:11.147
I'm gonna ask him though.

12:11.147 --> 12:12.314
- Maybe he did.

12:12.314 --> 12:14.483
Maybe he just
didn't tell anyone.

12:14.483 --> 12:16.652
- Well all I do know is
that all of my research

12:16.652 --> 12:18.654
about the pearl leads
me back to this writer,

12:18.654 --> 12:21.532
so apparently he's the expert.

12:24.827 --> 12:25.870
Done, ta-da.

12:50.811 --> 12:54.064
- So it's 16 hours
ahead in Fiji,

12:54.064 --> 12:56.859
which makes it 9:30
in the morning, yeah.

12:56.859 --> 12:57.943
She should be awake.

13:05.826 --> 13:06.577
- Hello?

13:06.577 --> 13:08.245
- Hey Serita, hi.

13:08.245 --> 13:09.830
It's Colin Page, do you--

13:09.830 --> 13:12.166
- Colin, it's so nice to
hear your voice again.

13:12.166 --> 13:12.958
How's New York?

13:12.958 --> 13:14.627
- Well, New York is New York.

13:14.627 --> 13:15.586
How's Fiji?

13:15.586 --> 13:17.338
- Beautiful as always.

13:17.338 --> 13:21.550
- Well, do you remember all
those conversations we had

13:21.550 --> 13:23.552
when you trying to
get me to come to Fiji

13:23.552 --> 13:25.596
while I was researching my book?

13:25.596 --> 13:26.764
- How could I forget?

13:26.764 --> 13:27.806
- And do you remember

13:27.806 --> 13:30.601
that you said if I
were to come to Fiji

13:30.601 --> 13:33.521
that you would show me your
great grandfather's journal?

13:33.521 --> 13:35.731
I'm hoping it might
provide some clues

13:35.731 --> 13:37.650
as to where the pearl might be.

13:37.650 --> 13:39.443
- Let me guess.

13:39.443 --> 13:40.486
You're coming to Fiji.

13:40.486 --> 13:42.321
- Yes I am.

13:42.321 --> 13:44.990
- Wonderful, I can finally
put a face to the voice.

13:44.990 --> 13:46.992
- I'm really looking
