1:17:53.752 --> 1:17:55.462
- Hey, welcome back.

1:17:56.922 --> 1:18:00.967
- Sharon, I'm, I'm sorry.

1:18:00.967 --> 1:18:03.095
I messed up again.

1:18:03.095 --> 1:18:06.223
And I completely
understand why Ben

1:18:06.890 --> 1:18:08.809
is the better candidate
for this promotion

1:18:08.809 --> 1:18:09.976
and if you wanna fire me--

1:18:09.976 --> 1:18:10.977
- Fire you?

1:18:12.104 --> 1:18:14.481
Why would I wanna fire
my new Creative Director?

1:18:14.481 --> 1:18:15.774
- You're not gonna fire me?

1:18:17.859 --> 1:18:19.027
I'm the new...

1:18:20.153 --> 1:18:22.656
Okay, but I didn't get
any pictures of the pearl.

1:18:22.656 --> 1:18:23.698
- Well, how could you?

1:18:23.698 --> 1:18:24.533
You didn't find it.

1:18:24.533 --> 1:18:25.951
- Well your voicemail.

1:18:25.951 --> 1:18:27.786
- Oh, complete miscommunication.

1:18:27.786 --> 1:18:29.538
Colin's agent thought
he'd found it,

1:18:29.538 --> 1:18:32.332
but turns out it was
bad cell reception.

1:18:32.332 --> 1:18:34.209
Anyway, it doesn't matter.

1:18:34.209 --> 1:18:38.255
What I really need is a photo
of you and Colin together.

1:18:38.255 --> 1:18:39.381
- Us?

1:18:39.381 --> 1:18:40.340
- For the cover.

1:18:41.716 --> 1:18:43.677
You do have some
of those, right?

1:18:43.677 --> 1:18:45.846
- Yeah, yeah, I've got some.

1:18:45.846 --> 1:18:48.974
- This is hands down the best
cover story we've ever done.

1:18:51.643 --> 1:18:52.728
Didn't he send it to you?

1:18:52.728 --> 1:18:54.646
- Uh, no.

1:18:54.646 --> 1:18:56.398
- Well I'm emailing it now.

1:18:56.398 --> 1:18:57.816
You need to read this.

1:19:09.411 --> 1:19:11.204
- In pursuit of a magical pearl

1:19:11.204 --> 1:19:14.583
hidden deep in the lush
rainforests of Viti Levu,

1:19:14.583 --> 1:19:17.127
I found something
completely unexpected.

1:19:18.253 --> 1:19:20.505
- After a
challenging three day hike

1:19:20.505 --> 1:19:23.592
with a charming and brilliant
photographer named Alex,

1:19:23.592 --> 1:19:26.470
and our two guides,
I add my name

1:19:26.470 --> 1:19:29.514
to the long list of
adventurers and lovers

1:19:29.514 --> 1:19:32.225
hoping to lay weary eyes
on a rare blue pearl

1:19:32.225 --> 1:19:33.643
that hundreds of years ago,

1:19:33.643 --> 1:19:36.396
disappeared into the
swirling, stormy sea.

1:19:37.272 --> 1:19:38.899
A pearl that now lies somewhere

1:19:38.899 --> 1:19:41.777
in a sun-kissed valley
paradise waiting to be found.

1:19:43.445 --> 1:19:45.489
Alex and I never
found the pearl.

1:19:46.281 --> 1:19:49.159
But the quest offered us
something more precious.

1:19:50.118 --> 1:19:51.953
It's only when we
open our hearts,

1:19:51.953 --> 1:19:54.039
ready to risk the unknown,

1:19:54.039 --> 1:19:56.208
that life's treasures
reveal themselves.

1:19:56.958 --> 1:20:00.295
And our hearts can love
a thousand times more

1:20:00.295 --> 1:20:01.671
than we ever imagined.

1:20:02.547 --> 1:20:05.550
And if you believe that
there's magic out there,

1:20:06.927 --> 1:20:08.094
it's yours to find.

1:20:08.804 --> 1:20:11.139
Alex knew that all along.

1:20:11.139 --> 1:20:14.559
And she inspired me to go on
a different kind of journey.

1:20:14.559 --> 1:20:17.813
No, I didn't find the
legendary blue pearl,

1:20:17.813 --> 1:20:20.148
but I found out who I want to be

1:20:20.982 --> 1:20:22.484
and who I want to be with.

1:20:23.610 --> 1:20:28.865
And in the end, love is the
greatest adventure of all.

1:20:32.452 --> 1:20:34.621
- Alex, I
have a delivery for you.

1:20:34.621 --> 1:20:35.914
Should I bring them up?

1:20:37.249 --> 1:20:38.208
- Yeah, thank you.

1:20:48.009 --> 1:20:49.636
- Hello?

1:20:49.636 --> 1:20:50.637
- Hi.

1:20:50.637 --> 1:20:51.513
- Hey Alex.

1:20:51.513 --> 1:20:53.265
It's nice hearing your voice.

1:20:54.599 --> 1:20:56.017
- I read your article.

1:20:56.017 --> 1:20:58.061
- Yeah and what did
you think of it?

1:20:59.688 --> 1:21:02.607
- Well, some of the
technical details

1:21:02.607 --> 1:21:03.733
didn't ring so true for me.

1:21:03.733 --> 1:21:04.651
- Ha, ha, ha.

1:21:08.446 --> 1:21:09.573
You're a funny girl.

1:21:12.450 --> 1:21:14.661
Some conversations are
better had in person

1:21:14.661 --> 1:21:17.330
than well, with flowers.

1:21:18.582 --> 1:21:20.709
- Did you mean everything
you said in that article?

1:21:20.709 --> 1:21:24.337
- Alex, I'm standing
in your office

1:21:24.337 --> 1:21:27.382
with rare flowers from Fiji,

1:21:27.382 --> 1:21:30.635
which I think officially makes
me a international smuggler.

1:21:33.013 --> 1:21:33.930
Yes.

1:21:35.432 --> 1:21:37.392
I meant every single word.

1:21:46.943 --> 1:21:48.862
- I just want you to
know that sometimes

1:21:48.862 --> 1:21:50.113
I'm not organized.

1:21:50.113 --> 1:21:51.197
- I like that.

1:21:51.197 --> 1:21:54.451
- And I don't ever,
ever wanna make a list.

1:21:54.451 --> 1:21:55.285
- Check.

1:21:56.036 --> 1:21:57.120
- And I don't like tea.

1:21:57.120 --> 1:21:59.581
- Ooh, all right, we're
working on that one.

1:21:59.581 --> 1:22:01.291
- And--
- And?

1:22:01.291 --> 1:22:03.209
- In the legend, it
says that only true love

1:22:03.209 --> 1:22:05.587
can find the pearl
and in your article,

1:22:05.587 --> 1:22:06.671
you said we didn't.

1:22:08.632 --> 1:22:09.716
- Hold on.

1:22:17.724 --> 1:22:19.809
It's not the blue pearl.

1:22:20.769 --> 1:22:21.686
But it's ours.

1:22:31.696 --> 1:22:35.158
That's that.

1:22:35.158 --> 1:22:38.620
- It's the most beautiful
pearl I have ever seen.

1:22:38.620 --> 1:22:41.039
- No, you are.

1:22:59.808 --> 1:23:00.850
Come on.

1:23:00.850 --> 1:23:02.727
Hurry up, I'm dying
to explore the reef.

1:23:02.727 --> 1:23:04.729
- Okay, okay, I just
wanna finish this chapter.

1:23:04.729 --> 1:23:07.107
- You know I could tell
you how it ends, right?

1:23:09.818 --> 1:23:11.444
- Don't you dare.

1:23:15.990 --> 1:23:16.825
- Come on.
